#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1. For example [[!wikipedia Machine Identification Code desc=\"printer tracking\n"
"dots\"]], printing imperfections, or intentional misspellings\n"
msgstr ""
"1. Par exemple des [[!wikipedia_fr Code d'identification de machine desc=\"points de suivi\n"
"d'imprimante\"]], des imperfections d'impression ou des erreurs d'orthographe intentionnelles\n"

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "System requirements"
msgstr "Configuration requise"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*Dangerzone* requires a lot of memory in the computer and space in your\n"
"Persistent Storage because it relies on [[!wikipedia Containerization\n"
"(computing) desc=\"software containers\"]] to manipulate dangerous files\n"
"securely.\n"
msgstr ""
"*Dangerzone* nécessite beaucoup de mémoire dans l'ordinateur et beaucoup d'espace sur votre\n"
"stockage persistant car il repose sur des [[!wikipedia Containerization\n"
"(computing) desc=\"conteneurs logiciels\"]] pour manipuler des fichiers dangereux\n"
"de façon sécurisée.\n"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "To install *Dangerzone*, you need at least:"
msgstr "Pour installer *Dangerzone*, vous avez besoin d'au moins :"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "- 8 GB of RAM"
msgstr "- 8 Go de mémoire vive"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "- 12 GB available in the Persistent Storage"
msgstr "- 12 Go disponibles dans le stockage persistant"

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing *Dangerzone*"
msgstr "Installation de *Dangerzone*"

#. type: Plain text
msgid "To install *Dangerzone* as additional software in Tails, you have to:"
msgstr ""
"Pour installer *Dangerzone* comme logiciel supplémentaire dans Tails, vous "
"devez :"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "[[Configure the *Dangerzone* APT repository|dangerzone#configure]]"
msgstr "[[Configurer le dépôt APT de *Dangerzone*|dangerzone#configure]]"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "[[Install the *Dangerzone* package|dangerzone#install]]"
msgstr "[[Installer le paquet *Dangerzone*|dangerzone#install]]"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "[[Convert a test document|dangerzone#test]]"
msgstr "[[Convertir un document de test|dangerzone#test]]"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<h2 id=\"configure\">Configure the <i>Dangerzone</i> APT repository</h2>\n"
msgstr "<h2 id=\"configure\">Configurer le dépôt APT de <i>Dangerzone</i></h2>\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"When starting Tails, [[set up an administration password|doc/first_steps/"
"welcome_screen/administration_password]]."
msgstr ""
"Lors du démarrage de Tails, [[définissez un mot de passe d'administration|"
"doc/first_steps/welcome_screen/administration_password]]."

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Choose **Applications&nbsp;▸ Persistent Storage** to open the Persistent "
"Storage settings."
msgstr ""
"Choisissez **Applications&nbsp;▸ Stockage persistant** pour ouvrir les "
"paramètres du stockage persistant."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   Create a Persistent Storage if you don't have one already.\n"
msgstr "   Créez un stockage persistant si vous n'en avez pas déjà un.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   Make sure that the **Additional Software** feature is enabled.\n"
msgstr "   Assurez-vous que la fonctionnalité **Logiciels supplémentaires** est activée.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   Close the Persistent Storage settings.\n"
msgstr "   Fermez les paramètres du stockage persistant.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Choose **Applications&nbsp;▸ Utilities&nbsp;▸ Terminal** to open a terminal "
"without administration rights."
msgstr ""
"Choisissez **Applications&nbsp;▸ Utilitaires&nbsp;▸ Terminal** pour ouvrir "
"un terminal sans les droits d'administration."

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Execute the following command to open the configuration of your Persistent "
"Storage in the *Text Editor* with administration rights."
msgstr ""
"Exécutez la commande suivante pour ouvrir la configuration de votre stockage "
"persistant dans l'*Éditeur de texte* avec les droits d'administration."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "       gnome-text-editor admin:///live/persistence/TailsData_unlocked/persistence.conf\n"
msgstr "       gnome-text-editor admin:///live/persistence/TailsData_unlocked/persistence.conf\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   Add the following line to store the configuration of third-party APT\n"
"   repositories in your Persistent Storage.\n"
msgstr ""
"   Ajoutez la ligne suivante pour enregistrer la configuration de dépôts APT\n"
"   tiers dans votre stockage persistant.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "       /etc/apt/sources.list.d\tsource=apt/sources,link\n"
msgstr "       /etc/apt/sources.list.d\tsource=apt/sources,link\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   Add the following line to store *Podman* containers in your Persistent\n"
"   Storage. [*Podman*](https://podman.io/) is the containerization technology\n"
"   used by *Dangerzone*.\n"
msgstr ""
"   Ajoutez la ligne suivante pour enregistrer les conteneurs *Podman* dans votre stockage\n"
"   persistant. [*Podman*](https://podman.io/) est la technologie de conteneurisation\n"
"   utilisée par *Dangerzone*.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "       /home/amnesia/.local/share/containers\tsource=podman\n"
msgstr "       /home/amnesia/.local/share/containers\tsource=podman\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   Save your changes and close the *Text Editor*.\n"
msgstr "   Sauvegardez vos changements et fermez l'*Éditeur de texte*.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Choose **Applications&nbsp;▸ System Tools&nbsp;▸ Root Terminal** to open a "
"terminal with administration rights."
msgstr ""
"Choisissez **Applications&nbsp;▸ Outils système&nbsp;▸ Terminal "
"superutilisateur** pour ouvrir un terminal avec les droits d'administration."

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Execute the following commands to configure the *Dangerzone* repository as "
"additional APT repository."
msgstr ""
"Exécutez les commandes suivantes pour configurer le dépôt de *Dangerzone* "
"comme un dépôt APT supplémentaire."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <p class=\"command-root\">mkdir /live/persistence/TailsData_unlocked/apt/sources</p>\n"
msgstr "   <p class=\"command-root\">mkdir /live/persistence/TailsData_unlocked/apt/sources</p>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <p class=\"command-root\">ln -s /usr/share/tails/apt/dangerzone.sources /live/persistence/TailsData_unlocked/apt/sources/</p>\n"
msgstr "   <p class=\"command-root\">ln -s /usr/share/tails/apt/dangerzone.sources /live/persistence/TailsData_unlocked/apt/sources/</p>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <div class=\"caution\">\n"
msgstr "   <div class=\"caution\">\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   <p>We include this sources file in Tails for convenience, but installing\n"
"   <i>Dangerzone</i> relies on the APT repository hosted by <a\n"
"   href=\"https://freedom.press/\">Freedom of the Press Foundation</a>.\n"
"   As a consequence:</p>\n"
msgstr ""
"   <p>Par commodité nous incluons dans Tails le fichier des sources, mais l'installation de\n"
"   <i>Dangerzone</i> dépend d'un dépôt APT hébergé par la<a\n"
"   href=\"https://freedom.press/\">Freedom of the Press Foundation</a>.\n"
"   Par conséquent :</p>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   <ul>\n"
"   <li>You need to trust the packages from this repository not to break the\n"
"   security of your Tails.</li>\n"
"   <li><i>Dangerzone</i> might stop working in Tails outside of the control of\n"
"   the Tails team.</li>\n"
"   </ul>\n"
msgstr ""
"   <ul>\n"
"   <li>Vous devez faire confiance aux paquets de ce dépôt pour ne pas casser la\n"
"   sécurité de votre Tails.</li>\n"
"   <li><i>Dangerzone</i> pourrait arrêter de fonctionner dans Tails en dehors du contrôle de\n"
"   l'équipe de Tails.</li>\n"
"   </ul>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   </div>\n"
msgstr "   </div>\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "Restart Tails."
msgstr "Redémarrez Tails."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<h2 id=\"install\">Install the <i>Dangerzone</i> package</h2>\n"
msgstr "<h2 id=\"install\">Installer le paquet <i>Dangerzone</i></h2>\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "[[Connect to the Tor network|doc/anonymous_internet/tor]]."
msgstr "[[Connectez-vous au réseau Tor|doc/anonymous_internet/tor]]."

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Execute the following commands to install the `dangerzone` package and its "
"dependencies."
msgstr ""
"Exécutez les commandes suivantes pour installer le paquet `dangerzone` et "
"ses dépendances."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <p class=\"command-root\">apt update</p>\n"
msgstr "   <p class=\"command-root\">apt update</p>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <p class=\"command-root\">apt install dangerzone fuse-overlayfs uidmap</p>\n"
msgstr "   <p class=\"command-root\">apt install dangerzone fuse-overlayfs uidmap</p>\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"After the packages are installed, a notification appears to ask if you want "
"to install `dangerzone`, `fuse-overlayfs`, and `uidmap` every time you start "
"Tails in the future."
msgstr ""
"Une fois les paquets installés, une notification apparaît pour vous demander "
"si vous voulez installer `dangerzone`, `fuse-overlayfs` et `uidmap` chaque "
"fois que vous démarrerez Tails à l'avenir."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   Choose to **Install Every Time**.\n"
msgstr "   Choisissez d'**Installer à chaque fois**.\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "Close the *Root Terminal*."
msgstr "Fermez le *Terminal superutilisateur*."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "<h2 id=\"test\">Convert a test document</h2>\n"
msgstr "<h2 id=\"test\">Convertir un document de test</h2>\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Choose **Applications&nbsp;▸ Office&nbsp;▸ Dangerzone** to start "
"*Dangerzone*."
msgstr ""
"Choisissez **Applications&nbsp;▸ Bureautique&nbsp;▸ Dangerzone** pour "
"démarrer *Dangerzone*."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   When started for the first time, *Dangerzone* installs its container.\n"
msgstr "   Lors de son premier démarrage, *Dangerzone* installe son conteneur.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   This operation can take several minutes.\n"
msgstr "   Cette opération peut prendre plusieurs minutes.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   After the setup finishes, *Dangerzone* opens.\n"
msgstr "   Une fois la configuration terminée, *Dangerzone* s'ouvre.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   Click the button **Select suspicious documents**.\n"
msgstr "   Cliquez sur le bouton **Select suspicious documents**.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   [[!img dangerzone.png link=\"no\" class=\"screenshot\" alt=\"\"]]\n"
msgstr "   [[!img dangerzone.png link=\"no\" class=\"screenshot\" alt=\"\"]]\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"Select a simple document to test the conversion process, like an empty "
"*LibreOffice* document or an image."
msgstr ""
"Sélectionnez un document simple pour tester le processus de conversion, par "
"exemple un document *LibreOffice* vide ou une image."

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   Converting this first document can also take several minutes. After this\n"
"   first document, converting other documents will be faster.\n"
msgstr ""
"   La conversion de ce premier document peut également prendre plusieurs minutes. Après ce\n"
"   premier document, la conversion des autres documents sera plus rapide.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <div class=\"bug\">\n"
msgstr "   <div class=\"bug\">\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   <p>If converting fails with the error <span class=\"code\">Unknown error code\n"
"   '125'</span>, restart Tails and try again.</p>\n"
msgstr ""
"   <p>Si la conversion échoue avec l'erreur <span class=\"code\">Unknown error code\n"
"   '125'</span>, redémarrez Tails et réessayez.</p>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"   <p><i>Dangerzone</i> needs a lot of available RAM when running for the first\n"
"   time. Restarting Tails frees as much RAM as possible.</p>\n"
msgstr ""
"   <p><i>Dangerzone</i> a besoin d'une grande quantité de mémoire vive lorsqu'il fonctionne pour la première\n"
"   fois. Le redémarrage de Tails libère autant de mémoire vive que possible.</p>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "   <p><i>Dangerzone</i> requires at least 8 GB of RAM to install.</p>\n"
msgstr "   <p><i>Dangerzone</i> nécessite au moins 8 Go de RAM pour l'installation.</p>\n"

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid ""
"After the conversion finishes, the original document is moved to a new "
"*unsafe* folder and the name of the safe document that has been created "
"includes *safe*. For example:"
msgstr ""
"Une fois la conversion terminée, le document d'origine est déplacé vers un "
"nouveau dossier *unsafe* et le nom du document sûr qui a été créé inclut "
"*safe*. Par exemple :"

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"       ├── document-safe.odt\n"
"       └── unsafe\n"
"           └── document.odt\n"
msgstr ""
"       ├── document-safe.odt\n"
"       └── unsafe\n"
"           └── document.odt\n"
